OL,3,CWolverhampton mum pleads people to
OL,4,Cgive up ninja swords before ban
OL,6,FAs part of the Government's new knife
OL,7,Fsurrender scheme, anti-knife crime
OL,8,Fcampaigner Faron Paul, of FazAmnesty,
OL,9,Fwill tour London, the West Midlands
OL,10,Fand Greater Manchester in an "amnesty
OL,11,Fvan" to help get rid of dangerous
OL,12,Fblades.
OL,14,FMr Paul added: "By taking this service
OL,15,Fdirectly into communities, I hope we
OL,16,Fcan reach more individuals, encourage
OL,17,Fpositive decisions, and help reduce
OL,18,Fthe number of harmful items on our
OL,19,Fstreets."
